parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and severe loss of steering control can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle's front end wobbles violently
the steering wheel shakes
and the vehicle may pull to one side
making it difficult to control. This occurs when driving over bumps
uneven road surfaces
or at speeds above 45-60 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The power steering pump stops working
making it difficult to steer the vehicle
especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of steering components can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes violently
the vehicle wobbles
and the steering system fails
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high voltage battery can cause a vehicle fire, even when the ignition is off, which can result in increased risk of occupant injury, injury to persons outside the vehicle, and property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience a loss of electrical power
stalls
or shut down while driving
and may display warning messages such as "Service Charging System." The vehicle may also be unable to charge or start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The software update issues can cause the vehicle to run rough, experience fluctuating charging indicators, and display warning lights, which can lead to a loss of power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience rough idling
fluctuating charging indicators
and warning lights
and may be unable to shift gears or accelerate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Availability and Recall Repair Delays
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving recall repair parts can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, posing a risk to occupants and others, and can also result in financial losses due to the inability to use the vehicle as intended.
symptoms: Vehicle owners may experience delays in receiving recall repair parts
leading to extended periods of time without a functioning vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, the failure can lead to a vehicle fire, resulting in increased risk of occupant injury and/or injury to persons outside the vehicle, as well as property damage.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
burning clutch smell
transmission slipping while shifting gears
warning lights illuminating indicating clutch overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The "death wobble" can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes violently
the vehicle veers into another lane
the front wheels feel like they are going to come off the axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of motive power can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a warning message indicating a loss of performance
the engine shuts down
the vehicle will not restart
the vehicle will not accelerate above a certain RPM.
